  "prompt": "Which are the top startups in India?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, several startups in India have gained significant attention and recognition due to their innovation, growth, and impact across various sectors. Here\u2019s a list of some of the top startups in India:\n\n1. **Byju's** - An ed-tech platform that offers online tutoring and learning materials for students.\n\n2. **Oyo Rooms** - A hospitality startup that provides budget accommodation options across the globe.\n\n3. **Zomato** - A food delivery and restaurant review platform that operates in several countries.\n\n4. **Paytm** - A digital payments platform that offers services ranging from mobile payments to financial services and e-commerce.\n\n5. **Swiggy** - Another food delivery service that competes with Zomato but also offers grocery delivery through Swiggy Instamart.\n\n6. **Razorpay** - A fintech company that provides payment solutions for businesses, including payment gateways and financial management tools.\n\n7. **Flipkart** - Originally an e-commerce startup, now a major player in the market, especially after being acquired by Walmart.\n\n8. **Ola Cabs** - A ride-hailing service that operates in India and several international markets.\n\n9. **CRED** - A fintech platform that rewards users for paying their credit card bills on time.\n\n10. **Nykaa** - An e-commerce platform specializing in beauty and wellness products.\n\n11. **Urban Company** - A service marketplace that connects consumers with service professionals for home repairs, cleaning, and beauty services.\n\n12. **Meesho** - A social commerce platform that enables individuals and small businesses to sell products through social channels.\n\n13. **Cure.fit** - A health and wellness startup that offers fitness services, healthy food, and mental well-being solutions.\n\n14. **Lenskart** - An eyewear startup that provides a range of glasses, lenses, and eye care services.\n\n15. **Delhivery** - A logistics and supply chain services company that has grown rapidly in the e-commerce space.\n\nThese companies represent various industries such as technology, finance, e-commerce, and healthcare. The startup ecosystem in India is dynamic, with new companies emerging regularly, so the landscape may continue to evolve.",
